name: Elvish Scout
text: {G}, {T}: Untap target attacking creature you control. Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt to and dealt by it this turn.

editions.flavor:
"Even for Elves, they were stealthy little twerps. They'd taken our measure before we'd even seen them."
—Marshall Volnikov
Even one whose ears were closely tuned to the sounds of Havenwood could miss hearing a Scout move past.
Although the Elves of Havenwood lived in isolated villages, their swift communications allowed them to act as a single community.

name: Elvish Scrapper
text: {G}, {T}, Sacrifice Elvish Scrapper: Destroy target artifact.

editions.flavor: "The stories tell of a distant time when machines overran the forests, destroying everything that lived. That time will not come again."

name: Elvish Soultiller
text: When Elvish Soultiller dies, choose a creature type. Shuffle all creature cards of that type from your graveyard into your library.

editions.flavor: Mutated elves wondered if this was their final form, or if it was just another step.
